-- Austrian Skier Marcel Hirscher Wins World Cup Slalom Event
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-01-27T16:42:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-27/austrian-skier-marcel-hirscher-wins-world-cup-ski-slalom-event.html
Austria ’s skier Marcel Hirscher won
today’s  World Cup  slalom event in front of a home crowd to
strengthen his lead in the overall standings.  He had a two-run time of 1 minute, 44.34 seconds at
Kitzbuehel, Austria, after posting the fastest second run.
Germany’s Felix Neureuther was runner-up, 0.77 second behind,
with Croatia’s Ivica Kostelic a further 0.16 second adrift.  “I tried my best, but it was pretty difficult,” Hirscher
told the ruling body FIS’s website after his first Kitzbuehel
victory. “I knew that Felix had an awesome run and that I would
need to give it my best to win.”  Hirscher leads overall with 1,035 points, while Aksel Lund Svindal of Norway has 921 and Ted Ligety of the U.S. has 736.
Hirscher leads the slalom category by 134 points from
Neureuther.  Kostelic had a fourth straight win in the combined event,
comprising a downhill yesterday and today’s slalom. He had a
total time of 3 minutes, 45.80 seconds. Alexis Pinturault and
Thomas Mermillod Blondin, both from France, were 1.26 seconds
and 2.56 seconds back, respectively. Kostelic and Pinturault
both have 180 points, with Blondin third on 96.  Tina Maze  won the World Cup women’s slalom event at Maribor
in her home country of Slovenia.  Maze clocked a combined time of 1 minute, 33.68 seconds for
the two runs, Sweden’s Frida Hansdotter was 0.86 second back in
second and Kathrin Zettel of Austria was third, a further 0.27
second behind.  Maze has 1,654 points in the overall standings, with Maria Hoefl-Riesch of Germany in second on 806.  Lindsey Vonn  is third
on 740. Mikaela Shiffrin of the U.S. tops the slalom event with
468 points, 13 ahead of Maze.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in  London  at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
